article.description: Pat Andree pumped in a career-best 30 points, all from behind the arc, to propel Lehigh to a 100-67 win over St. Francis (Pa) on Monday night.
article.headline: Andree's hot shooting pushes Lehigh past St. Francis 100-67
article.linkText: Andree's hot shooting pushes Lehigh past St. Francis 100-67
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- Pat Andree pumped in a career-best 30 points, all from behind the arc, to propel Lehigh to a 100-67 win over St. Francis (Pa) on Monday night. Andree finished 10 of 12 from 3-point range and tied a school record for most made 3s in a game. Tim Kempton and Austin Price added 21 points apiece and Kyle Leufroy had 13 for Lehigh, which shot 56 percent from the field. Kempton also grabbed 11 rebounds to get his sixth double-double of the season. Lehigh took the lead for good in the first half with a jumper from Leufroy that made it 10-8 and hung on for a 43-36 halftime advantage. Jordan Cohen's bucket early in the second half made it 56-46 and Lehigh continued to stretch the double-figure advantage the rest of the way. Isaiah Blackmon led St. Francis with 13 points and Josh Nebo had 10.
